The All Progressives Congress (APC) has released the timetable and schedule of activities for the November 6 Anambra State Governorship Election. It also fixed the conduct of primary election for June 26. APC said the sale of expression of interest and nomination forms will be available for prospective aspirants from April 16 to June 8, adding that nomination form is pegged at N20million, while expression of interest form costs N2.5 million, totalling N22.5 million. It said female aspirants and physically challenged aspirants are, however, to pay 50 per cent of the prescribed fees for the position. A statement by the partyâ€™s Director of Organisation, Prof. Al-Mustapha, Ussiju Medaner, said the screening of aspirants would hold on June 10, just as it fixed the publication of claims and objections for June 12.